YAOUNDE, Feb. 14 (Xinhua) -- Cameroonian Prime Minister Joseph Dion Ngute on Monday met with visiting Serbian Foreign Minister Nikola Selakovic to discuss ways to enhance bilateral relations. During the meeting, the Serbian FM who is visiting Cameroon for the first time, highlighted the importance of further strengthening and diversifying relations between the two nations in future especially in the economic field. "Actually it is the first one (visit) of a high official of Serbia taking place after 38 years. Both countries are having good traditions of friendship but the chances for better cooperation especially in the field of economy are almost not used at all. The main purpose of this very visit is trying to renovate our relations," Selakovic told reporters in the capital Yaounde after the meeting.  â– 